Kraton™ D SBS Products




The Kraton D SBS family of polymers is versatile with a combination   of high strength, wide range of hardness, and low viscosity for easy   thermoplastic melt processing or processing in solution. The SBS block   copolymers are composed of blocks of styrene and butadiene. It is the   material of choice for footwear and the modification of bitumen/asphalt.   It is also very useful in pressure sensitive adhesives, hot melt spray   diaper adhesives, construction adhesives, impact modification of styrenics, thermoformed clear rigid packaging, and compounds.


Note: If you are unable to locate the GHS Safety Data Sheet from the drop  down menu, please contact the Product Safety support team at product.safety@kraton.com
 



